  "texts": [
    "• LLM outputs are mostly used exactly as the models generate them.",
    "However, using parts of the output, or arranging several partial outputs in the pre-defined slots of a larger explanation template offers educators more flexibility for controlling the final explanation content.",
    "• • Quantitative evaluation of LLM responses does not necessarily reflect its quality for an education use case.",
    "Pedagogy experts pointed out in some of our interviews that several LLM-generated texts are not wrong, but they do not offer a high value-added to students.",
    "One expert expressed this idea as: \"[the chatbot response] is not wrong."
  ],
